1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:07,700
Before the Transformer, sequence models like Recurrent Neural Networks processed information sequentially, creating

2
00:00:07,799 --> 00:00:12,500
bottlenecks for long sequences and hindering parallelization. While Convolutional Networks offered some parallel

3
00:00:12,599 --> 00:00:17,299
computation, they struggled with capturing long-range dependencies efficiently. The groundbreaking 'Attention Is All You

4
00:00:17,399 --> 00:00:22,099
Need' paper introduced the Transformer, a novel architecture that entirely removed recurrence and convolutions. This

5
00:00:22,199 --> 00:00:26,899
model aimed to boost training speed and handle distant relationships by relying solely on attention mechanisms.

6
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:33,649
At its core, attention is a mechanism that allows a model to weigh the importance of different parts of the input

7
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:38,899
sequence when processing each element. It functions by mapping a 'query' to a set of 'key-value' pairs. The query vector

8
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:44,149
interacts with all key vectors, determining a relevance score for each. These scores are then used to compute a weighted

9
00:00:44,250 --> 00:00:49,399
sum of the value vectors, forming the output, allowing the model to focus on pertinent information.

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:57,100
The Transformer primarily uses Scaled Dot-Product Attention, where the dot products of queries and keys are scaled by

11
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:03,300
the square root of the key's dimension, before applying a softmax function. This scaling prevents large dot products

12
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:09,500
from leading to vanishing gradients. Multi-Head Attention extends this by running several attention mechanisms in

13
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:15,700
parallel on different linear projections of the input. This enables the model to jointly attend to information from

14
00:01:15,799 --> 00:01:21,900
various representation subspaces and different positions, enhancing its ability to capture diverse dependencies.

15
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:27,600
The Transformer's Encoder block is responsible for processing the input sequence into a rich, contextual

16
00:01:27,700 --> 00:01:31,800
representation. Each identical encoder layer consists of two main sub-layers: a Multi-Head Self-Attention mechanism,

17
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:36,000
which allows tokens to interact with all other tokens in the input sequence, and a Position-wise Feed-Forward Network.

18
00:01:36,099 --> 00:01:40,200
Crucially, each sub-layer employs residual connections followed by layer normalization, aiding in gradient flow and

19
00:01:40,299 --> 00:01:44,400
stabilizing training in deep networks.

20
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:50,566
The Decoder block generates the output sequence, one token at a time. It also features identical layers, but with three

21
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:55,233
sub-layers. The first is a Masked Multi-Head Self-Attention, which prevents the decoder from attending to future tokens

22
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:59,900
during training, mimicking inference. The second is an Encoder-Decoder Attention layer, where queries come from the

23
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,566
decoder's previous layer, and keys/values come from the encoder's output, enabling the decoder to focus on relevant

24
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:09,233
parts of the input. Finally, a Position-wise Feed-Forward Network processes the combined information before a final

25
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:13,900
softmax layer predicts the next token.

26
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:19,599
Since the Transformer processes all tokens in parallel without recurrence or convolutions, it inherently loses

27
00:02:19,699 --> 00:02:23,799
information about the order of the sequence. To compensate, Positional Encodings are added to the input embeddings.

28
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:28,000
These encodings are generated using sine and cosine functions of varying frequencies, allowing the model to

29
00:02:28,099 --> 00:02:32,199
differentiate between token positions and learn relative positional relationships. This simple yet ingenious addition

30
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:36,400
provides the necessary sequential context to the attention mechanisms.

31
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:43,733
The Transformer's architecture proved revolutionary, achieving state-of-the-art results on machine translation tasks,

32
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:49,566
significantly outperforming previous recurrent and convolutional models in terms of quality. Its reliance on attention

33
00:02:49,666 --> 00:02:55,400
enabled unparalleled parallelization during training, drastically reducing computation time and allowing for larger

34
00:02:55,500 --> 00:03:01,233
models. By efficiently capturing long-range dependencies, the Transformer laid the groundwork for countless

35
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:07,066
advancements, becoming the foundational architecture for nearly all modern large language models and a cornerstone of

36
00:03:07,166 --> 00:03:12,900
contemporary AI research.
